<div style="padding: 10px;">
    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <br />
    <h3>By participating in volunteer work and reaching out to those around us, the Arcin’ Round Volunteer Program strives to enrich the quality of life and provide the joy of service to the participants of The Arc of Grays Harbor, as well as, the surrounding community.</h3>

    <br />
    <h3>Meetings are held every second Tuesday of the month at 6:00 pm at the Southshore Mall Community Room.</h3>
    <br />


    <h2>Goals of the Program</h2>
    <ol>
    <li><h3>Participate in FOUR major volunteer projects a year! Partner with other groups; such as, Relay for Life, Friends of Shafer and Lake Sylvia, Habitat for Humanity.</h3></li>

    <li><h3>Help build member and business partnerships for The Arc of Grays Harbor.  More support means a greater voice!</h3></li>

    <li><h3>Volunteer at The ArcGH events and set up volunteer opportunities within The ArcGH itself.</h3></li>

    <li><h3>Develop volunteer opportunities with other agencies in the county; such as, Coastal Harvest, PAWS, etc.</h3></li>

    </ol>
    <h2>Membership Guidelines</h2>
    <br />
    <h3>Anyone is invited to become a member of the Arcin’ Round Volunteer Program.  In order to be an official voting member a participant must, at the VERY LEAST….</h3>
    <ol>
    <li><h3>Participate in one of the four major volunteer projects each year.</h3></li>
    <li><h3>Attend 25% of the monthly meetings.</h3></li>
    <li><h3>Volunteer 10 hours of their time within The Arc of Grays Harbor or at a program or organization outside of The ArcGH.</h3></li>
    </ol>
    <br />
